FBIS3-59082 "drweu017_n_94002" FBIS-WEU-94-017 Document Type:Daily Report 26 Jan 1994 NORDIC COUNTRIES Finland Russian Arms Imports To Offset International Debt LD2501152694 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Swedish 1300 GMT 25 Jan 94 LD2501152694 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network Language: Swedish Article Type:BFN [Text] Russia's debt to Finland, which runs into the billions, will be partly reduced by Finland buying weapons from Russia. This involves weapons and ammunition worth 450 million Finnish Marks granted in a supplementary budget last year. Finland is to receive portable anti-aircraft missiles, among other things. The deliveries will be specified in a couple of weeks, the Defense Ministry says. The total Russian debt to Finland is just over 6 billion Finnish Marks.
